The article is about the inauguration of Dr. Shogan as the first woman to be appointed Archivist of the United States. The speaker, the First Lady, highlights the importance of preserving history and the role of the National Archives in capturing the story of the country. She mentions key historical documents and events, both positive and negative, that are housed in the Archives. The First Lady emphasizes the need to learn from the past and the significance of having diverse voices and perspectives in shaping the national memory. She congratulates Dr. Shogan on her appointment and expresses excitement for the future stories that will be preserved under her leadership.